wgputoy: tell wasm-pack's wasm-opt to enable bulk-memory features

After cargo finishes the wasm32 build, wasm-pack runs binaryen's wasm-opt
to shrink the output. Rust 1.82+ defaults wasm32-unknown-unknown to the
`bulk-memory` target feature, so the .wasm contains `memory.copy` /
`memory.fill` ops; recent binaryen wasm-validator rejects them unless
`--enable-bulk-memory` (and `--enable-bulk-memory-opt`) is passed.

The pinned commit's Cargo.toml has no `[package.metadata.wasm-pack.profile.*]`
block (verified at 60d0bec); appending one is safe and additive.

Tracked: github.com/utensil/forest/issues/54 item 2 (new).
To drop: upstream PR to wgputoy adding the metadata block, then bump
prep_wasm hash + flake pin.

diff --git a/Cargo.toml b/Cargo.toml
--- a/Cargo.toml
+++ b/Cargo.toml
@@ -78,3 +78,6 @@ wasm-bindgen-test = "0.3.31"
 # Tell `rustc` to optimize for small code size.
 opt-level = "s"
 strip = true
+
+[package.metadata.wasm-pack.profile.release]
+wasm-opt = ['-O', '--enable-bulk-memory', '--enable-bulk-memory-opt']
